            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I joined this school in 10th grade, and though my time here was short—just one year—I felt right at home.  While I didn't have much time to build deep friendships, I did connect with some wonderful teachers.  This school, with its unique character, fostered a welcoming atmosphere.\nThe teachers were kind, understanding, and possessed a great sense of humor.  Even though my interactions with them were brief, I could tell how dedicated they were to their profession and their students.  It was clear that each teacher, no matter how strict, held a special place in the students' hearts. They were committed to ensuring no one was left behind and worked hard to help every student succeed.  The sports teachers, especially, were a lot of fun to be around.  Volleyball is definitely a serious sport here.\nMy favorite spot on campus was the art room. Though not large, it was the loveliest place, with beautifully painted walls and student artwork displayed everywhere. Time seemed to slow down there, and a sense of calm always prevailed. The art teachers were incredibly supportive and always lifted my spirits.\nThe principal is a strict but fair man with strong beliefs and values. He doesn't tolerate nonsense, a fact that becomes clear upon meeting him.  He's incredibly knowledgeable and enjoys sharing interesting facts and insights. While he might seem intimidating at times, he genuinely cares about his students' well-being, a fact that I think many students don't fully appreciate.  He seems to have a particular fondness for quick-witted individuals who also possess strong moral character.\nI highly recommend this school, especially for younger children. I believe they'll receive an excellent foundation here.",
